ğŸ”— WSGI vs ASGI
ğŸµ Flask (WSGI)

WSGI = Web Server Gateway Interface.
Synchronous nature â†’ one request at a time.
Blocking I/O â†’ slow when many clients connect.

Framework: Flask + Werkzeug + Gunicorn (WSGI-based).

âš ï¸ Disadvantage: High latency, cannot handle real-time tasks (e.g., WebSockets).
âš¡ FastAPI (ASGI)

ASGI = Asynchronous Server Gateway Interface.
Handles concurrent requests efficiently (Async I/O).
Built on Starlette â†’ async support.
Uvicorn / Hypercorn = high-performance ASGI servers.
Allows real-time, ML, DL, WebSocket, streaming.

ğŸ­ Analogy

ğŸ½ï¸ Flask = Waiter â†’ takes one customer order at a time, kitchen waits until order is served.
âš¡ FastAPI = Smart Restaurant System â†’ multiple waiters, chefs, and async processing â†’ handles 100s of customers simultaneously.

